ch.qos.logback.classic.android

Class SQLiteAppender

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.qos.logback.core.spi.ContextAwareBase
      • ch.qos.logback.core.UnsynchronizedAppenderBase<ILoggingEvent>
        • ch.qos.logback.classic.android.SQLiteAppender
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Appender<ILoggingEvent>, ContextAware, FilterAttachable<ILoggingEvent>, LifeCycle

    public class SQLiteAppender
extends UnsynchronizedAppenderBase<ILoggingEvent>
    SQLiteAppender is a logback appender optimized for Android SQLite. It requires no JDBC as it uses the built-in Android SQLite API.
    Since:
    1.0.11
